==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Organoleptic
<hw>Or`ga*no*lep"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>organoleptique</ets>, fr. Gr. <?/ an organ + <?/ to lay hold
of.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>Making an impression upon an
organ; plastic; -- said of the effect or impression produced by any
substance on the organs of touch, taste, or smell, and also on the
organism as a whole.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Organological</ent>⟦br⟧
